ate.This third edition of the leading textbook on New York politics combines historical, legal, statistical, and journalistic sources with the candid perspectives of legislators, lobbyists, and other public officials. Critical updates and new information include: an analysis of the rise and fall of Governor Andrew Cuomo; coverage of growing demographic diversity in New York State and its government; and the impact of unified government with the legislature and executive controlled by the Democratic Party.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 4aGOVERNMENT. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / Middle Atlantic (DC, DE, MD, NJ, NY, PA).2bisacsh  alegislative process in New York state, New York state budget process, political corruption in new York state, Rise and fall of Governor Andrew Cuomo, demographic diversity in New York state government.1 aManiscalco, Anthony, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPole, Antoinette, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150176729640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501767296423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501767296/original  a978-3-11-075183-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-1